
Ruby if-else statement is used to test the specified condition.

-------------- if statement ---------------

Syntax : 
if (condition) 
  # statements to be executed 
end  

------------ if-else statement ------------

if’ statement used to execute block of code when the condition is true and ‘else’ statement is used to execute a block of code when the condition is false.

Syntax:

if(condition)  
  # code if the condition is true  
else  
  # code if the condition is false  
end  

------------ if-elsif-else statement ------------

Syntax:

if(condition1)
  # code if the condition1 is true
elsif
  # code if the condition2 is true
else
  # code if the condition3 is true
end

------------ ternary operator/statement ------------

(?:) - It is a conditional operator which is a shorthand version of the if-else statement.

  Syntax : 

  condition ? first_expression : second_expression

  Lets say name = 'Vikram', age = 30, role = 'employee'

  Statement: name == "Vikram" && age != 32 ? 'Role = Employee' : 'Role = Non-Employee'

=> Refer Program if_else.rb



